trend_summary: Across the time series the highway corridor attracted steady warehouse and retail infill, replacing several wooded parcels and enlarging parking lots. Residential blocks stayed mostly unchanged, though a few vacant lots filled with single-family homes. Road widening and new roundabouts improved access. Tree cover shrank modestly, yet golf course and major green buffers persisted.
notable_changes: Expansion of warehouse/industrial roofs along both sides of the main highway interchange.
Clearing of two wooded patches in the northwest and southeast for new commercial lots.
Addition of new slip roads and a roundabout improving highway access.
Incremental residential infill on previously vacant suburban lots.
Noticeable reduction of tree canopy near the industrial corridor while golf course stays intact.
